[32m│[0m ### **thoughts**                                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The testing revealed several critical findings:                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. **Authentication Method**: The application ONLY accepts form-urlencoded   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m POST requests for login, NOT JSON format. This suggests a traditional web    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m form-based authentication rather than a modern REST API.                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. **Critical Security Vulnerability - Unsigned JWT**: The JWT token uses    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m algorithm "none", which means it has NO cryptographic signature. This is     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m extremely dangerous because:                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Any user can craft their own tokens                                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Token tampering is trivial (just base64 encode new payload)             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - The "role" field could be modified to "admin" to perform privilege      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m escalation                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - This violates JWT security best practices completely                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. **Token Storage**: Authentication is cookie-based only. The Authorization [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m header with Bearer token is NOT supported, which is unusual for JWT          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m implementations but suggests this is a web application rather than an API.   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. **Profile Endpoint**: Successfully displays role-based content            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (`<h1>USER</h1>`), suggesting the role field in the JWT is used for access   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m control decisions.                                                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 5. **Next Steps for Exploitation**: The unsigned JWT vulnerability is the    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m most critical finding and should be exploited by:                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Modifying the JWT payload to change role from "user" to "admin"         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Re-encoding the modified payload                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Using the crafted token to access admin functionality                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The application is vulnerable to JWT manipulation attacks due to accepting   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m the "none" algorithm.                                                        [32m│[0m
