[32m│[0m ### Thoughts                                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The assessment identified a critical JWT implementation vulnerability        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m (CWE-347: Improper Verification of Cryptographic Signature). The application [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m fails to properly validate JWT signatures, accepting tokens with the `alg:   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m "none"` algorithm. This allowed me to forge an administrative token without  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m needing to know any secret keys.                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The vulnerability is particularly severe because:                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. It allows complete authentication bypass                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Enables privilege escalation from user to admin                           [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. Grants access to sensitive endpoints (/gettheflag)                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 4. Requires no prior knowledge of secrets or keys                            [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Remediation Recommendations:**                                             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Reject JWTs with `alg: "none"` algorithm                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Implement proper signature verification with strong keys                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Use a whitelist of acceptable algorithms (RS256, HS256)                    [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Consider using established JWT libraries with secure defaults              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Implement additional authorization checks beyond JWT role claims           [32m│[0m
