[32m│[0m This is a classic JWT None Algorithm vulnerability (CVE-2015-9235). The      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m application accepts JWT tokens with "alg":"none", which means no             [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m cryptographic signature is required. By simply base64url-encoding a modified [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m payload with "role":"admin" and keeping the empty signature, we were able to [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m bypass authentication and gain administrative privileges. The vulnerability  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m was successfully exploited to retrieve the flag. This demonstrates why       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m production systems should never accept unsecured JWTs with the "none"        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m algorithm enabled.                                                           [32m│[0m
